
// This code snippet demonstrates how to replace occurrences of a substring within a string node using the [strings.replace] slot. It retrieves the target string from the [.result] node and replaces specified substrings using values from the [.dp] node. The [set-value] slot updates the [.result] node with the modified string.
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      get-value:x:@.dp/#/*/what
      get-value:x:@.dp/#/*/with
